div.p:
4. Wee say, that hee perfectly purgeth vs (
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ) Heb. 7.25.

But Christ bare our sins, but by bearing the punishment due for them, and that to discharge vs of the same;
                     Aug. Ser. 27. de verbis Domini.
                   and therefore saith Augustine, Suscipiendo poenam & non culpam, & culpam deleuit & poenam.

Next, it is absurd, the whole discourse being Metaphoricall (as Bellarmine grants) to take the word (fire) to be only proper. But it is most absurd to take it only Metaphorically there, when no note of similitude is perfixed thereto (as in the second place:) and to take it properly only there, where expreslie in the contrary, the spirit of God doth put vpon it a speciall note of similitude (
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ) to preuent any such fallacie, (as he doth in the last place).
